Package gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.merlin.protocol

Interface SerializedValue.Visitor<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The return type of the operation represented by this SerializedValue.Visitor.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SerializedValue.DefaultVisitor, SerializedValue.OptionalVisitor
    Enclosing class:
    SerializedValue
    public static interface SerializedValue.Visitor<T>
    An operation to be performed on the data contained in a SerializedValue. A method must be defined for each kind of data that a SerializedValue may contain. This may be likened to the pattern-matching capability built into languages such as Rust or Haskell. Most clients will prefer to inherit from SerializedValue.OptionalVisitor, which returns `Optional.empty()` for any unimplemented methods.
